<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\companions\companion_aligern_stage3</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>89</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't have anything to say about the monument. Don't ask."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>""</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Inifere... another castoff, another stain. Look, I've got to ask. Why do you think so many of your kind cause so much pain?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>""</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>He crosses his arms and waits.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>{diffident}"I appreciate the chance to stop by Ormen's monument. Been too long since I visited."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why not?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why did you want to see it, then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No worries. I wanted to talk to you about something else, though."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I didn't say that I didn't want to see it. Just that I don't want to talk about it. At least not to you, not right now. Maybe later."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>He gives you a slow, steady look. "You know why. At least, I hope you do. We'll talk about it soon enough. Let's just get to Miel Avest, all right?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fine."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm sorry about what happened to your family, Aligern."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Well, I've got to keep you happy."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>""</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Shock registers momentarily on his face, replaced quickly with a short smile. "Appreciate it. Come on. We've got to get to Miel Avest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Because we're born into danger? Because the Sorrow hunts us all from the moment of our birth? Because so many people hate us for the accident of our birth and the crimes of our creator? I don't know, Aligern. Why don't you tell me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>He grimaces. "About what I expected to hear, I suppose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>He holds up his hands. "Hold on, I didn't say you -"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Oh, and why not? I mean, look at me. I'm the White Death. I've killed armies of men. I've made my share of orphans. I served the old Memovira of the Bloom. It's not like my hands are clean."

She leans in and whispers, "But it's not like yours are either, are they?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>For a moment, it appears that he is going to strike her. For her part, she seems supremely unconcerned.

He breathes out. "Point taken." He turns to you. "What's your take then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Natural inclinations, maybe."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why do so many ordinary humans cause so much pain?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No idea. But then, I don't know how the Changing God made us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But ordinary people also bring good. I'm trying to think of a castoff known for good deeds and greatness, and I can't."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Heh. Maybe with a healthy side of disdain for society." He shakes his head. "Anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It doesn't mean they don't exist."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're not an admirer of the way I conduct my business, then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>He shrugs. "You do what needs to be done."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I appreciate the vote of confidence."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's basically all anyone does."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then maybe the question is, why do so many castoffs get into situations where what has to be done is so terrible? I mean, founding a murderous cult is... that's extreme."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Maybe some people are just broken from the start. Worth thinking about."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You don't know what pressures drove him. Have some empathy."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A lot of things happen in the moment, and cascade into larger effects."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yeah, maybe." 

He scratches his nose. "Maybe it's time get moving, eh?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've had a lot of stress in my life, but I've never gone and started a death cult."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>He scowls. "They sure do." He spits. "Let's get moving."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>He barks a laugh.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hmm. Maybe. Doesn't seem like your type is really cut out for a life of anonymity, though. Anyway. Let's get moving, eh?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You know that castoffs don't always seek attention, right?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you know about the Valley, anyway?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the Valley again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Give me your opinion on Miel Avest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Give me your opinion on Miel Avest again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's talk about you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's talk about you again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How are you holding up?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's talk about our traveling companions."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I think it's best we part."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's move on."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>He looks around, and his mouth is tight. "Every one of these people has been touched by the Changing God. Every one. And look at them. They all seem scarred and fragile." Something that's almost pity touches his face. "All of you are suffering."

His voice hardens again. "But it doesn't compare to the suffering you all have brought to the world."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I feel for all of you. Surrounded by beauty, and all you do is fight."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Burial place for countless civilizations. Not in the Valley itself, but below it. My aldeia's memorial is here. It used to be peaceful, serene. A place where people could come and think for a spell. I've never been to the Necropolis. Never really had any urge to see it."

He laughs softly. "None of my dead left any remains anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Not much to say. Lots of history to think on, legacies remembered for a while and then forgotten."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you think we should do next?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>""</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>""</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Aadiriis... she's given me a lot to think about." He looks at you levelly, though he seems a little shaken. 

"She's the first of your kind who doesn't make me fear for my life. The first who makes me want to be better. And I'm going to try."

He looks down at the tattoos on his arms. "Doesn't mean I don't want answers, mind you. But... I'm going to work with you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's finish up what we need to get done. I've said what I needed to say. Now we need to figure out where we go from here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>He frowns. "And a fine job you're doing with it. Come on. We've got to get to Miel Avest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Regardless. I appreciate it." He adjusts his jacket. "Let's get moving."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Not a bother. It was on our way anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's a memorial here in the Valley that I'd like to visit. You know. If we get a chance."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>He shrugs. "Go to Miel Avest. Seems like that's where your answers are." 

His voice hardens. "Mine too."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"While we're in the Valley... I've got a place I'd like to visit. My village's monument. I haven't been there for a while, need to pay my respects. It's not far from here, so it's not really out of the way."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll see what we can do."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Only if we've got time."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Appreciate it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We don't have time for this. Mourn the dead on your own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>He stares at you, but says nothing.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let's."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>He crosses his arms and waits.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's your story?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I want to talk about you again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>He chuckles. "For a second there, I thought I heard you say you wanted to leave me. Here. In one of the Ninth World's many hells with no way out, not even death."

His smile drops off his face quickly. "Of course you *didn't* say that. So I'll forget you did."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>He wriggles a finger in and out of his ear. "Damn, I'm getting old. I heard you say it again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
